AND TOAST THE CROISSANT DOUGH

1277
00:52:59,609 --> 00:53:01,278
He presses down on it like that.

1278
00:53:01,344 --> 00:53:03,113
I didn't know he could do that.

1279
00:53:03,180 --> 00:53:04,881
He's pressing it down with a pot.

1280
00:53:04,948 --> 00:53:07,517
-Yes, but the pot is a bit smaller.
-Yes?

1281
00:53:07,584 --> 00:53:09,686
He might miss a few spots.

1282
00:53:09,753 --> 00:53:13,290
Chef Hyun-suk caught onto that.

1283
00:53:13,356 --> 00:53:15,358
How many servings is this?
You seem to make a lot.

1284
00:53:15,425 --> 00:53:16,760
-For now…
-Is it okay?

1285
00:53:16,826 --> 00:53:18,762
-I have to use only the pretty pieces.
-Pretty pieces.

1286
00:53:19,629 --> 00:53:21,364
He'll only use pretty pieces.

1287
00:53:21,431 --> 00:53:24,834
He's going to make something
by using croissant dough.

1288
00:53:25,902 --> 00:53:27,370
POONG GRABS GREEN ONION

1289
00:53:28,305 --> 00:53:29,439
PRETENDS TO PUT IT IN THE POT

1290
00:53:30,006 --> 00:53:31,107
HE FEINTS!

1291
00:53:32,776 --> 00:53:35,111
THE CAMERA
WAS COMPLETELY DECEIVED

1292
00:53:35,178 --> 00:53:36,179
He's making chili oil.

1293
00:53:36,246 --> 00:53:39,549
-What's Poong doing? I knew it.
-Chili oil.

1294
00:53:39,616 --> 00:53:41,451
He rarely ever skips that.

1295
00:53:41,518 --> 00:53:42,886
-He always makes chili oil?
-Yes.

1296
00:53:42,953 --> 00:53:44,955
That's his foundation.

1297
00:53:45,021 --> 00:53:46,389
He starts by making that.

1298
00:53:46,456 --> 00:53:48,325
-It's spicy red pepper powder.
-Will you make it spicy?

1299
00:53:48,391 --> 00:53:50,227
-I like it.
-Do you like spicy food?

1300
00:53:50,293 --> 00:53:51,428
-I love it.
-He loves it.

1301
00:53:51,494 --> 00:53:53,730
He's adding Cheongyang pepper.

1302
00:53:53,797 --> 00:53:56,066
LOOK AT HOW THE WINNER CHOPS

1303
00:53:56,132 --> 00:53:57,334
He's chopping.

1304
00:53:57,400 --> 00:53:59,236
-Poong isn't so bad.
-He's chopping.

1305
00:53:59,302 --> 00:54:00,537
He really is a cook.

1306
00:54:00,604 --> 00:54:03,673
Yes, he's good at using
his Chinese kitchen knife.

1307
00:54:03,740 --> 00:54:05,275
He's good at chopping even two and three.

1308
00:54:05,342 --> 00:54:07,043
He chops two at the same time!

1309
00:54:07,110 --> 00:54:08,612
RELAXED

1310
00:54:08,678 --> 00:54:11,348
Before, the thickness was never even.

1311
00:54:11,414 --> 00:54:14,184
-But the sizes look similar now.
-Yes.

1312
00:54:14,251 --> 00:54:15,852
-He's good.
-He must've practiced.

1313
00:54:16,419 --> 00:54:17,587
Turn down the heat.

1314
00:54:17,654 --> 00:54:18,888
THE CHILI OIL

1315
00:54:19,456 --> 00:54:21,291
-The chili oil.
-It's the chili oil.

1316
00:54:21,358 --> 00:54:22,826
He'll probably use just the oil.

1317
00:54:22,892 --> 00:54:25,028
He's straining the oil? This is fun.

1318
00:54:25,095 --> 00:54:26,463
His hands are trembling.

1319
00:54:26,529 --> 00:54:27,664
DOWN!

1320
00:54:27,731 --> 00:54:29,499
The color looks wonderful.

1321
00:54:29,566 --> 00:54:31,735
He made it so quickly.

1322
00:54:31,801 --> 00:54:34,104
-It's fun to watch both channels.
-Right?

1323
00:54:34,170 --> 00:54:35,605
It's fun to watch both.

1324
00:54:36,106 --> 00:54:38,208
-What's that? An egg?
-An onion.

1325
00:54:38,275 --> 00:54:39,442
CHUCKLES

1326
00:54:39,509 --> 00:54:40,510
Egg?

1327
00:54:40,577 --> 00:54:43,880
That chopping skill. Nice job, Nam-no.

1328
00:54:43,947 --> 00:54:46,082
-He's very delicate.
-That detail.

1329
00:54:46,149 --> 00:54:47,951
-Yes.
-That was cool.

1330
00:54:48,018 --> 00:54:50,053
He's chopping it finely.

1331
00:54:52,722 --> 00:54:54,691
It's as if I'm playing it at double speed.

1332
00:54:54,758 --> 00:54:57,127
-Whoa, he's getting faster.
-Yes.

1333
00:54:57,193 --> 00:54:58,895
It's a spectacle!

1334
00:54:58,962 --> 00:55:00,096
He's moving very fast.

1335
00:55:00,163 --> 00:55:01,531
Caper.

1336
00:55:03,133 --> 00:55:05,101
What's he using?

1337
00:55:05,168 --> 00:55:07,203
-Olives.
-Olives.

1338
00:55:07,937 --> 00:55:10,040
SHOWING OFF

1339
00:55:10,740 --> 00:55:12,776
He just chopped olives.

1340
00:55:14,010 --> 00:55:16,680
-What did he get? Garlic?
-Garlic cloves.

1341
00:55:17,247 --> 00:55:19,983
HE MINCES GARLIC WITH A BLENDER

1342
00:55:20,050 --> 00:55:23,286
4. MAKE GARLIC OIL
WITH MINCED GARLIC AND OLIVE OIL

1343
00:55:23,353 --> 00:55:25,155
POURING

1344
00:55:27,223 --> 00:55:29,959
HE USES A TORCH
TO LIGHT THE STOVE

1345
00:55:30,527 --> 00:55:33,330
YOON NAM-NO, THE FIERY GUY

1346
00:55:36,533 --> 00:55:37,734
MILK

1347
00:55:37,801 --> 00:55:40,003
-What are you doing, Poong?
-Cheese.

1348
00:55:40,070 --> 00:55:43,106
-Cheese and?
-I'm making a dip.

1349
00:55:43,173 --> 00:55:45,375
He's making a dip like nacho cheese.

1350
00:55:45,442 --> 00:55:47,277
Nacho cheese tastes delicious.

1351
00:55:47,344 --> 00:55:49,079
He's melting the cheese.

1352
00:55:49,145 --> 00:55:50,880
They know a good bar snack

1353
00:55:50,947 --> 00:55:52,615
because they also love to drink.

1354
00:55:52,682 --> 00:55:55,485
-Poong deep-fries the tofu thoroughly.
-Yes.

1355
00:55:55,552 --> 00:55:56,953
It'll make the texture chewy.

1356
00:55:57,020 --> 00:56:00,357
Everything is good when it's deep-fried.
Nothing tastes bad when it's fried.

1357
00:56:00,423 --> 00:56:01,991
-You're right.
-Everything tastes good.

1358
00:56:02,058 --> 00:56:03,727
-He knows what a good bar snack is.
-He does.

1359
00:56:03,793 --> 00:56:07,130
Poong's deep-fried tofu

1360
00:56:07,197 --> 00:56:09,799
almost looks like Korean taffy, yeot.

1361
00:56:09,866 --> 00:56:13,970
Well, it kind of looks like taffy,
but also like the bean curd in <i>mala </i>soup.

1362
00:56:14,037 --> 00:56:16,606
-I don't like <i>mala</i>.
-You don't?

1363
00:56:16,673 --> 00:56:17,974
He doesn't like <i>mala</i>.

1364
00:56:18,041 --> 00:56:20,076
-Don't make <i>mala</i>.
-No to <i>mala</i>.

1365
00:56:20,143 --> 00:56:21,678
Don't do it while I'm nice.

1366
00:56:21,745 --> 00:56:23,580
He doesn't like <i>mala</i>.

1367
00:56:23,646 --> 00:56:25,281
-I'm not using it.
-<i>Mala</i>.

1368
00:56:25,348 --> 00:56:26,516
I'm not using <i>mala</i>.

1369
00:56:27,751 --> 00:56:28,752
CROISSANT DOUGH

1370
00:56:28,818 --> 00:56:30,353
REVEALED!

1371
00:56:31,588 --> 00:56:33,123
Were they toasted?

1372
00:56:33,189 --> 00:56:34,524
They would be.

1373
00:56:34,591 --> 00:56:35,792
It looks so good.

1374
00:56:36,393 --> 00:56:37,627
Whoa.

1375
00:56:38,561 --> 00:56:39,763
GIGGLING

1376
00:56:39,829 --> 00:56:42,332
-It was too hot.
-The handles were hot too.

1377
00:56:42,399 --> 00:56:45,268
If even Nam-no does that,
it means it's really hot.

1378
00:56:45,335 --> 00:56:46,736
