He likes that fermented taste.

1410
00:58:04,214 --> 00:58:06,583
-That looks too salty.
-It won't be.

1411
00:58:06,649 --> 00:58:09,752
Sugar.

1412
00:58:11,120 --> 00:58:16,426
Poong, it looks like
you're making sweet and spicy sauce.

1413
00:58:16,493 --> 00:58:17,961
-You're correct!
-I am?

1414
00:58:18,027 --> 00:58:19,162
-I see.
-That's right.

1415
00:58:19,229 --> 00:58:20,830
That's the sweet and spicy sauce.

1416
00:58:22,265 --> 00:58:23,500
Damn it.

1417
00:58:23,566 --> 00:58:25,435
Why are you saying, "Damn it"?
What went wrong?

1418
00:58:25,502 --> 00:58:27,003
No, it's going well.

1419
00:58:28,204 --> 00:58:30,940
-He's chopping that.
-He's making thin slices.

1420
00:58:31,007 --> 00:58:33,209
-He's making tofu fillets.
-It's like tofu noodles.

1421
00:58:33,276 --> 00:58:34,611
Yes.

1422
00:58:34,677 --> 00:58:35,678
WHAT'S HE MAKING?

1423
00:58:35,745 --> 00:58:36,746
It's okay.

1424
00:58:36,813 --> 00:58:39,516
Poong, are you trying to shape them
like French fries?

1425
00:58:39,582 --> 00:58:41,017
You're right. Bingo.

1426
00:58:41,084 --> 00:58:43,520
-Will he fry those again?
-He will.

1427
00:58:43,586 --> 00:58:45,522
He's frying those again.

1428
00:58:45,588 --> 00:58:47,724
-It'll be crunchier.
-He double fries them like French fries.

1429
00:58:47,790 --> 00:58:49,526
This is a great idea.

1430
00:58:49,592 --> 00:58:53,263
-Like French fries.
-And he's serving them with chili sauce.

1431
00:58:53,329 --> 00:58:55,532
It's a perfect snack with beer.

1432
00:58:55,598 --> 00:58:58,134
-They look like French fries.
-They do.

1433
00:58:58,701 --> 00:59:00,036
He's using a gridiron.

1434
00:59:01,471 --> 00:59:04,407
RIB EYE IS ON THE STAGE

1435
00:59:04,474 --> 00:59:06,342
-It's literally on fire.
-What's he broiling?

1436
00:59:06,409 --> 00:59:07,510
My goodness.

1437
00:59:07,577 --> 00:59:09,812
It's the meat he put into the garlic oil.

1438
00:59:09,879 --> 00:59:10,880
Meat?

1439
00:59:10,947 --> 00:59:12,549
The meat?

1440
00:59:12,615 --> 00:59:14,350
The one that went into the garlic oil.

1441
00:59:14,417 --> 00:59:16,386
-It's burning.
-Just lightly.

1442
00:59:16,452 --> 00:59:18,454
Oh, like <i>tataki</i>.

1443
00:59:18,521 --> 00:59:21,624
-A bar owner sure is different.
-He is.

1444
00:59:21,691 --> 00:59:23,459
-This looks good.
-He's different.

1445
00:59:23,526 --> 00:59:25,929
-The meat is ready.
-It looks great.

1446
00:59:25,995 --> 00:59:26,996
Was it broiled well?

1447
00:59:27,063 --> 00:59:28,131
You'll chop those?

1448
00:59:29,098 --> 00:59:30,733
I see. Wait, what?

1449
00:59:30,800 --> 00:59:33,703
-He's making thin slices.
-He's making slices too.

1450
00:59:33,770 --> 00:59:35,371
How's the croissant doing?

1451
00:59:35,438 --> 00:59:36,539
Yes, the croissant.

1452
00:59:38,808 --> 00:59:40,610
-The heat.
-The heat.

1453
00:59:40,677 --> 00:59:41,945
It's hot.

1454
00:59:43,580 --> 00:59:45,515
-It's good.
-It's okay.

1455
00:59:45,582 --> 00:59:46,916
Just leave it there.

1456
00:59:46,983 --> 00:59:50,453
You have five minutes left.
Jung-hwan, please step out.

1457
00:59:50,520 --> 00:59:52,555
Damn it. I can't make that dip.

1458
00:59:52,622 --> 00:59:54,657
You can probably just strain it.

1459
00:59:54,724 --> 00:59:58,161
Poong, I think I heard you say,
"Damn it," like 200 times.

1460
00:59:58,227 --> 00:59:59,262
You still have time.

1461
00:59:59,329 --> 01:00:01,698
These tofu slices look like French fries.

1462
01:00:01,764 --> 01:00:03,833
-They do?
-They look the same.

1463
01:00:04,500 --> 01:00:07,637
-He's dicing the beef finely.
-They look like chips.

1464
01:00:07,704 --> 01:00:09,305
-He's dicing the rib eye.
-He is.

1465
01:00:09,372 --> 01:00:12,775
The smoky smell is amazing here.
I can smell it everywhere.

1466
01:00:12,842 --> 01:00:14,010
Four minutes.

1467
01:00:14,077 --> 01:00:15,912
-He used tomatoes.
-Caviar.

1468
01:00:16,412 --> 01:00:17,914
TRUFFLE OLIVE SAUCE, CAVIAR

1469
01:00:17,981 --> 01:00:20,817
He mixed truffle and caviar.

1470
01:00:20,883 --> 01:00:22,685
He put in both truffle and caviar.

1471
01:00:22,752 --> 01:00:25,655
-Beef, caper, truffle, and caviar?
-Truffle.

1472
01:00:25,722 --> 01:00:27,457
He threw in everything delicious.

1473
01:00:28,124 --> 01:00:30,293
AND THE GARLIC OIL!

1474
01:00:30,860 --> 01:00:32,261
MIX AND MIX

1475
01:00:33,262 --> 01:00:34,864
TAKES A BITE

1476
01:00:36,699 --> 01:00:38,601
Man, it's a bit salty.

1477
01:00:38,668 --> 01:00:42,171
Jung-hwan, the tofu sticks
look like French fries.

1478
01:00:42,238 --> 01:00:43,306
They look the same.

1479
01:00:43,373 --> 01:00:45,108
-Can you try one?
-Shall I?

1480
01:00:45,174 --> 01:00:46,643
It still looks hot.

1481
01:00:47,944 --> 01:00:49,078
Just eat it as you're told!

1482
01:00:49,145 --> 01:00:51,981
-We don't have time.
-You're an entertainer, so eat it.

1483
01:00:52,048 --> 01:00:53,916
Man. I'll eat it.

1484
01:00:53,983 --> 01:00:55,985
Try it and see if it's like French fries.

1485
01:00:56,052 --> 01:00:58,321
Will the tofu sticks
taste like French fries?

1486
01:00:58,388 --> 01:00:59,622
The tofu.

1487
01:00:59,689 --> 01:01:01,791
It looks exactly like French fries.

1488
01:01:02,759 --> 01:01:04,894
Let the viewers see it too.

1489
01:01:04,961 --> 01:01:07,897
What will it taste like? Come on.

1490
01:01:07,964 --> 01:01:09,799
Eat it, Jung-hwan!

1491
01:01:09,866 --> 01:01:12,869
-Stop blowing on it. There's no time!
-Do it for the show!

1492
01:01:12,935 --> 01:01:14,303
It's too hot.

1493
01:01:14,370 --> 01:01:15,405
It's not hot.

1494
01:01:15,471 --> 01:01:16,606
-It must be good.
-What's it like?

1495
01:01:16,673 --> 01:01:17,874
It must be savory.

1496
01:01:17,940 --> 01:01:19,575
Are you craving some beer?

1497
01:01:20,276 --> 01:01:21,577
I am craving some beer!

1498
01:01:23,312 --> 01:01:25,281
-It's subtle and delicious.
-It is?

1499
01:01:25,348 --> 01:01:27,216
Poong must have the lead so far.

1500
01:01:27,283 --> 01:01:29,185
-It's been fried well.
-I see.

1501
01:01:29,252 --> 01:01:30,253
-He makes it work.
-It's good.

1502
01:01:30,319 --> 01:01:32,455
You have 2 minutes and 30 seconds!

1503
01:01:33,256 --> 01:01:35,158
The dip looks good with that.

1504
01:01:36,325 --> 01:01:38,461
-It's ruined.
-No, it's fine.

1505
01:01:39,095 --> 01:01:41,097
-Whoa.
-I'm sorry.

1506
01:01:41,931 --> 01:01:43,399
HAVE A TASTE OF MY DIP

1507
01:01:43,466 --> 01:01:44,600
It's fine.

1508
01:01:45,902 --> 01:01:47,603
TRUFFLE BRUSCHETTA SAUCE

1509
01:01:48,337 --> 01:01:49,439
SPLASH

1510
01:01:49,505 --> 01:01:51,174
Is something not going well?

1511
01:01:51,240 --> 01:01:52,308
No, I can do this.

1512
01:01:52,375 --> 01:01:55,044
He throws in random things
and tells himself that he can do it.

1513
01:01:57,413 --> 01:01:58,915
Chef Nam-no, what's… Huh?

1514
01:01:59,882 --> 01:02:01,617
-What's that?
-It smells like truffles.

1515
01:02:01,684 --> 01:02:03,019
Can you try that, Jung-hwan?

1516
01:02:03,086 --> 01:02:04,554
No! It's too salty.

1517
01:02:04,620 --> 01:02:06,622
That's why he's adding more meat.

1518
01:02:06,689 --> 01:02:08,725
-Oh, no.
-He's adding every piece of meat he has.

1519
01:02:08,791 --> 01:02:10,526
It smells strongly of truffles.

1520
01:02:11,527 --> 01:02:12,895
SHAKING AND MIXING

1521
01:02:13,996 --> 01:02:15,998
-So strain this?
-Yes, strain it.

1522
01:02:17,100 --> 01:02:19,001
POONG LISTENS TO WHAT HE SAYS

1523
01:02:19,068 --> 01:02:21,137
-It'll be hard.
-It's hard to strain cheese.

1524
01:02:21,204 --> 01:02:22,205
You have a minute!

1525
01:02:22,271 --> 01:02:24,140
-What's not working?
-Damn it!

1526
01:02:26,008 --> 01:02:27,176
Use this.

1527
01:02:27,243 --> 01:02:29,712
It won't be strained!

1528
01:02:29,779 --> 01:02:32,882
-Push down on it.
-He wanted to make it into a dip!

1529
01:02:32,949 --> 01:02:33,983
He should've melted it slowly,

1530
01:02:34,050 --> 01:02:36,319
but the cheese got scorched
over high heat.

1531
01:02:36,385 --> 01:02:38,254
Just serve it as is.

1532
01:02:38,321 --> 01:02:40,523
You can't strain that.

1533
01:02:40,590 --> 01:02:41,724
Use this.

1534
01:02:42,492 --> 01:02:43,893
It's too thick.

1535
01:02:43,960 --> 01:02:45,795
Hey, the croissant.

1536
01:02:46,763 --> 01:02:49,632
It looks hot. It must be hot, Nam-no.

1537
01:02:49,699 --> 01:02:52,135
You have a minute and 40 seconds!

1538
01:02:53,903 --> 01:02:57,006
POONG BEGINS TO SERVE THE DISH
WITH BARE HANDS

1539
01:02:57,507 --> 01:02:59,375
-Argh!
-It's too hot!

1540
01:02:59,909 --> 01:03:00,910
Whoa!

1541
01:03:00,977 --> 01:03:02,178
Things are hot on both sides.

1542
01:03:02,245 --> 01:03:05,381
How do you do this every single week?

1543
01:03:05,448 --> 01:03:07,683
What happened? I need to see the dip.

1544
01:03:08,251 --> 01:03:10,419
-I need to see the dip.
-Use this.

1545
01:03:10,486 --> 01:03:12,555
What about the sauce?

1546
01:03:13,322 --> 01:03:15,825
-What's this?
-He strained that.

1547
01:03:15,892 --> 01:03:18,327
-"What's this?"
-What's going on?

1548
01:03:18,394 --> 01:03:19,395
Use Tabasco if you want to.

1549
01:03:19,462 --> 01:03:23,166
-That doesn't look so…
-Look at that

1550
01:03:23,232 --> 01:03:24,233
Make it look pretty.

1551
01:03:24,300 --> 01:03:25,635
One minute.

1552
01:03:25,701 --> 01:03:26,936
It looks too rough.

1553
01:03:27,003 --> 01:03:29,305
-You have a minute left.
-There's not much time.

1554
01:03:29,372 --> 01:03:33,276
-Myung-soo appreciates the presentation.
-Two different flavors.

1555
01:03:33,342 --> 01:03:34,977
He'll get mad at you.

1556
01:03:35,044 --> 01:03:36,913
-The presentation?
-That's like a pub!

1557
01:03:36,979 --> 01:03:39,715
Poong, that's a pub snack!

1558
01:03:39,782 --> 01:03:41,350
It's like a pub!

1559
01:03:41,417 --> 01:03:44,086
-Poong!
-What's he sprinkling?

1560
01:03:44,153 --> 01:03:46,289
-Parsley.
-What is this, Poong?

1561
01:03:46,355 --> 01:03:47,523
Parsley.

1562
01:03:47,590 --> 01:03:49,959
You don't have much time left.

1563
01:03:50,026 --> 01:03:52,295
HE GOT THREE SLICES
OF RECTANGULAR CROISSANT

1564
01:03:52,795 --> 01:03:54,197
NAM-NO BEGINS
TO SERVE HIS DISH TOO

1565
01:03:54,263 --> 01:03:55,965
He begins to serve his dish.

1566
01:03:56,032 --> 01:03:57,700
THE RIB EYE TARTARE
GOES DOWN FIRST

1567
01:03:57,767 --> 01:04:00,436
One minute. You have one minute left.

1568
01:04:00,503 --> 01:04:02,171
Take your time. You're fine.

1569
01:04:02,238 --> 01:04:04,473
No, I have to make salad too.

1570
01:04:05,041 --> 01:04:08,244
MR. ANXIETY
IS RACING AGAINST TIME

1571
01:04:08,978 --> 01:04:10,346
TREMBLING

1572
01:04:10,413 --> 01:04:12,582
10. LAYER BEEF TARTARE
AND CROISSANT

1573
01:04:12,648 --> 01:04:15,451
TO FINISH MAKING
THE MILLE-FEUILLE

1574
01:04:15,518 --> 01:04:17,720
THE LAST PIECE!

1575
01:04:17,787 --> 01:04:19,155
Can you take this?

1576
01:04:20,156 --> 01:04:23,025
-Thirty seconds!
-Thirty seconds!

1577
01:04:23,092 --> 01:04:25,862
-Thirty seconds!
-The salad!

1578
01:04:25,928 --> 01:04:29,031
He's making salad
with 30 seconds of time left.

1579
01:04:29,098 --> 01:04:30,266
Twenty seconds!

1580
01:04:30,333 --> 01:04:34,036
-Twenty seconds!
-Can Nam-no make salad in 30 seconds?

1581
01:04:34,103 --> 01:04:35,605
Just serve it!

1582
01:04:36,439 --> 01:04:38,407
GIGGLING

1583
01:04:38,975 --> 01:04:40,543
BUT AT THIS RATE,
HE'D BE AS GOOD AS KIM POONG…

1584
01:04:40,610 --> 01:04:41,677
You can't help it.

1585
01:04:41,744 --> 01:04:42,979
He's a regular, so he understands.

1586
01:04:43,045 --> 01:04:45,681
-Twenty seconds!
-Twenty seconds!

1587
01:04:45,748 --> 01:04:48,050
HE PUTS IT INTO BOILING OIL

1588
01:04:48,117 --> 01:04:49,785
What are you frying?

1589
01:04:49,852 --> 01:04:52,555
-Capers.
-Capers.

1590
01:04:52,622 --> 01:04:55,892
-He's deep-frying capers. Ten seconds!
-This is so much fun.

1591
01:04:55,958 --> 01:04:59,228
-Nine. Eight. Seven.
-Nine. Eight. Seven.

1592
01:04:59,295 --> 01:05:02,164
-Six. Five. Four.
-Six. Five. Four.

1593
01:05:02,231 --> 01:05:05,167
-Three. Two. One.
-Three. Two. One.

1594
01:05:05,234 --> 01:05:06,802
It's over. Ring the bell.

1595
01:05:06,869 --> 01:05:08,571
POONG FINISHES POONG GOES ON

1596
01:05:08,638 --> 01:05:09,739
Poong finishes first.

1597
01:05:09,805 --> 01:05:11,040
Then it's Nam-no.

1598
01:05:11,107 --> 01:05:13,109
I didn't even cook,
but I was so nervous.

1599
01:05:13,175 --> 01:05:14,577
I have a feeling Poong's dish is

1600
01:05:14,644 --> 01:05:15,978
like a freebie on the house.

1601
01:05:16,045 --> 01:05:17,980
GIGGLING

1602
01:05:18,547 --> 01:05:21,017
May I please top it with some green onion?

1603
01:05:21,083 --> 01:05:24,086
The ones you had in the water?
The green onion.

1604
01:05:24,153 --> 01:05:26,222
Poong must give you a go sign.

1605
01:05:26,289 --> 01:05:28,391
-As a chef, I will let him do that.
-Yes?

1606
01:05:30,226 --> 01:05:31,627
I can show him that much mercy.

1607
01:05:31,694 --> 01:05:32,995
-Really?
-I won't do it.

1608
01:05:33,062 --> 01:05:34,964
Why not? Just top it.

1609
01:05:35,031 --> 01:05:37,199
Nam-no missed that.

1610
01:05:37,266 --> 01:05:38,334
The green onion.

1611
01:05:38,401 --> 01:05:41,804
Are these leftovers
from your previous guests?

1612
01:05:41,871 --> 01:05:44,974
-I'd say, "Why did you serve leftovers?"
-It's so cute.

1613
01:05:45,041 --> 01:05:48,411
How can you give me leftovers? Come on!

1614
01:05:48,477 --> 01:05:50,112
It's not like I ever forgot to pay!

1615
01:05:50,179 --> 01:05:52,715
And now, these two dishes are finished

1616
01:05:52,782 --> 01:05:56,519
to fill Myung-soo's order,
Grandpa Myung-soo, alone with beer.

1617
01:05:56,585 --> 01:05:58,187
IT WAS A HECTIC
AND PASSIONATE ROUND

1618
01:05:58,254 --> 01:05:59,822
That was amazing.

1619
01:05:59,889 --> 01:06:02,058
So do you like how it looks?

1620
01:06:02,124 --> 01:06:04,160
I don't really mind how it looks
when I drink alone,

1621
01:06:04,226 --> 01:06:06,262
but there is a dish
which I like the look of,

1622
01:06:06,329 --> 01:06:07,596
and one that I don't like.

1623
01:06:07,663 --> 01:06:10,099
-Is that so? I see.
-Yes.

1624
01:06:10,166 --> 01:06:12,501
-Don't I have to be honest? Should I lie?
-You're right.

1625
01:06:12,568 --> 01:06:14,236
-You're right.
-That's how things work.

1626
01:06:14,303 --> 01:06:16,072
You should try them now.

1627
01:06:16,739 --> 01:06:19,842
HALF PLAIN, HALF SEASONED

1628
01:06:20,943 --> 01:06:25,047
FRENCH FRIES MADE WITH TOFU

1629
01:06:25,815 --> 01:06:29,418
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
POONG GOES ON

1630
01:06:30,386 --> 01:06:33,923
This looks like a dish
made by a first-time pub owner.

1631
01:06:33,990 --> 01:06:37,560
Someone who opened up a pub
without any knowledge.

1632
01:06:37,626 --> 01:06:40,663
But it looks perfect for beer.

1633
01:06:40,730 --> 01:06:43,132
-It's a perfect dish for drinking alone.
-Drinking alone.

1634
01:06:43,199 --> 01:06:46,068
It's high in protein,
so I'm sure it'll be perfect.

1635
01:06:46,135 --> 01:06:48,671
Those aren't French fries, but tofu fries.

1636
01:06:48,738 --> 01:06:50,106
Tofu is good for you.

1637
01:06:50,172 --> 01:06:51,707
-I'll have some beer first.
-Some beer.

1638
01:06:51,774 --> 01:06:53,009
Server?

1639
01:06:53,075 --> 01:06:54,176
SERVER JUNG-HWAN GETS IT READY

1640
01:06:54,243 --> 01:06:56,112
I poured a perfect glass.

1641
01:06:56,178 --> 01:06:58,114
ASTONISHED

1642
01:06:58,180 --> 01:06:59,915
That's Jung-hwan the server.

1643
01:06:59,982 --> 01:07:01,884
-Here.
-That's for you.

1644
01:07:01,951 --> 01:07:04,220
Waiters at clubs would copy
soccer player names.

1645
01:07:04,286 --> 01:07:06,756
-Yes, the waiters did that.
-And we have Jung-hwan here.

1646
01:07:06,822 --> 01:07:08,858
-I'm Terius.
-I've seen Cho Yong-pil.

1647
01:07:08,924 --> 01:07:10,426
-There are two flavors.
-Yes?

1648
01:07:10,493 --> 01:07:13,396
One of them is just salted tofu fries,

1649
01:07:13,462 --> 01:07:14,930
so try that.

1650
01:07:14,997 --> 01:07:17,233
As for the dip…

1651
01:07:17,299 --> 01:07:19,335
Just look at it and not eat it.

1652
01:07:19,902 --> 01:07:22,238
-This one?
-It probably didn't turn out well.

1653
01:07:22,304 --> 01:07:24,106
-Have a sip of beer.
-Have some beer first.

1654
01:07:24,173 --> 01:07:26,175
HE DRINKS BEER
JUST LIKE HIS ORDER

1655
01:07:26,242 --> 01:07:28,077
He's serious about beer.

1656
01:07:28,144 --> 01:07:29,278
SO REFRESHING

1657
01:07:29,345 --> 01:07:31,580
He drinks that after work to chill out.

1658
01:07:31,647 --> 01:07:33,916
He says he has about eight cans of beer.

1659
01:07:33,983 --> 01:07:35,584
-After a tough day.
-That looks good.

1660
01:07:35,651 --> 01:07:39,555
-I hope it makes him crave more beer.
-Yes.

1661
01:07:39,622 --> 01:07:41,424
-So?
-He tries the plain one.

1662
01:07:41,490 --> 01:07:43,025
Fried tofu.

1663
01:07:43,092 --> 01:07:45,327
It must be nutty and delicious.

1664
01:07:45,394 --> 01:07:47,430
-Why?
-What does that mean?

1665
01:07:47,496 --> 01:07:48,931
-Is it good?
-Is it delicious?

1666
01:07:48,998 --> 01:07:51,400
I could feel him scoff.

1667
01:07:51,467 --> 01:07:54,170
-I don't think he likes it.
-It must be nutty.

1668
01:07:54,236 --> 01:07:55,404
Try it in different ways.

1669
01:07:55,471 --> 01:07:57,239
-He said that was like decoration.
-He's dipping it.

1670
01:07:57,306 --> 01:07:58,774
It's not going in.

1671
01:07:58,841 --> 01:07:59,842
He can't dip it.

1672
01:07:59,909 --> 01:08:01,677
Has the cheese thickened?

1673
01:08:01,744 --> 01:08:04,046
-It's the dip.
-He tries it again.

1674
01:08:04,113 --> 01:08:05,915
-It hardened.
-It's just cheese now.

1675
01:08:05,981 --> 01:08:07,650
The thickness wasn't right.

1676
01:08:07,716 --> 01:08:08,751
CHUCKLES

1677
01:08:08,818 --> 01:08:10,953
I think he'll say,
"Let's go to a different place."

1678
01:08:11,554 --> 01:08:12,855
Can I have the check?

1679
01:08:14,390 --> 01:08:16,959
-Can I have the check?
-Already? I see.

1680
01:08:17,026 --> 01:08:20,029
-Let me try the other one just in case.
-Yes.

1681
01:08:20,096 --> 01:08:22,064
-You fried this one too.
-Yes.

1682
01:08:22,131 --> 01:08:25,067
-It has to be at least average.
-Yes, of course. Huh?

1683
01:08:26,502 --> 01:08:27,937
-Does it taste different?
-He nods.

1684
01:08:28,003 --> 01:08:31,107
-Do they taste different?
-Do they?

1685
01:08:31,173 --> 01:08:33,042
-He's drinking beer.
-He keeps drinking it.

1686
01:08:33,109 --> 01:08:35,344
-He's craving beer.
-He keeps drinking.

1687
01:08:35,411 --> 01:08:36,612
He craved more beer.

1688
01:08:36,679 --> 01:08:38,347
AMAZED

1689
01:08:39,415 --> 01:08:41,317
-Poong Beer.
-He'll get an ad deal.

1690
01:08:41,383 --> 01:08:43,352
-It's good.
-It is?

1691
01:08:43,419 --> 01:08:45,387
-He'll get a beer ad.
-Thanks for the dish.

1692
01:08:45,454 --> 01:08:47,556
What do you mean? Wait.

1693
01:08:47,623 --> 01:08:50,259
Tell us what it's like.
Don't just end it there.

1694
01:08:50,326 --> 01:08:52,228
I was too into it just now.

1695
01:08:52,294 --> 01:08:53,729
You aren't here to drink beer.

1696
01:08:53,796 --> 01:08:56,298
-I'm sorry. I was too…
-Give us a review.

1697
01:08:56,365 --> 01:09:00,002
The fried tofu, the first one I had.

1698
01:09:00,069 --> 01:09:02,071
-Yes.
-It didn't taste like anything.

1699
01:09:02,138 --> 01:09:05,207
It felt like I was eating
a zero-calorie snack. Do you get it?

1700
01:09:05,274 --> 01:09:06,675
It must've tasted healthy.

1701
01:09:06,742 --> 01:09:10,746
-The more I chew it, it gets nuttier.
-It's tofu.

1702
01:09:10,813 --> 01:09:12,448
But I didn't crave beer after that.

1703
01:09:12,515 --> 01:09:14,416
You can use the dip, then.

1704
01:09:14,483 --> 01:09:16,185
I think it's better not to dip it.

1705
01:09:16,252 --> 01:09:18,854
-Is that so?
-It's already hard.

1706
01:09:18,921 --> 01:09:21,090
It's completely thickened.

1707
01:09:21,157 --> 01:09:22,591
TA-DA

1708
01:09:22,658 --> 01:09:24,793
-The sauce thickened.
-I see.

1709
01:09:24,860 --> 01:09:26,562
-The thickness.
-I couldn't dip it.

1710
01:09:27,129 --> 01:09:28,497
LAUGHS

1711
01:09:28,564 --> 01:09:29,565
COUGH

1712
01:09:29,632 --> 01:09:31,467
-But the sweet and spicy sauce is amazing.
-Sweet and spicy.

1713
01:09:31,534 --> 01:09:33,235
The sweet and spicy sauce
makes me crave more beer.

1714
01:09:33,302 --> 01:09:35,604
It's spicy, and it makes me crave beer.

1715
01:09:35,671 --> 01:09:40,042
I think it'll taste great
if you scoop some dip on the spicy one.

1716
01:09:40,109 --> 01:09:41,744
-Like this?
-Yes, that's it.

1717
01:09:41,810 --> 01:09:44,780
-Should I spread it like this?
-Yes, spread it like jam.

1718
01:09:44,847 --> 01:09:46,448
He's trying the cheese dip
with the sweet and spicy tofu.

1719
01:09:46,515 --> 01:09:47,683
It looks good.

1720
01:09:47,750 --> 01:09:50,386
-Is it good?
-You're good.

1721
01:09:50,452 --> 01:09:53,022
-Yes, he's good.
-Chef Hyun-suk.

1722
01:09:53,088 --> 01:09:55,891
-The sweet and spicy tofu is spicy.
-Yes.

1723
01:09:55,958 --> 01:09:58,894
So the savory cheese flavor
mixes well with that spiciness.

1724
01:09:58,961 --> 01:10:01,530
-I see.
-It's sweet, salty, and smooth.

1725
01:10:01,597 --> 01:10:04,500
-It's good. It's really good.
-It looks good.

1726
01:10:05,100 --> 01:10:08,604
A CLASSY COMBINATION
THAT'LL MAKE HIM CRAVE BEER

1727
01:10:09,271 --> 01:10:12,708
LAYERS OF CROISSANT
AND BEEF TARTARE

1728
01:10:13,776 --> 01:10:17,646
CHEF YOON NAM-NO'S
NO BEER LEFT BEHIND

1729
01:10:17,713 --> 01:10:19,081
Should I eat it with salad?

1730
01:10:19,148 --> 01:10:21,150
Grab the croissant piece,

1731
01:10:21,217 --> 01:10:23,752
then top it with beef tartare like canapé.

1732
01:10:24,553 --> 01:10:26,355
-What now?
-Put this on this.

1733
01:10:26,422 --> 01:10:28,023
Flip it over and put that on top.

1734
01:10:28,090 --> 01:10:30,159
Isn't this complicated?
I'm trying to drink alone at home.

1735
01:10:31,660 --> 01:10:34,096
You just need your hands. Like this.

1736
01:10:34,930 --> 01:10:37,132
Do I just take one piece?
I can't hear anything he says.

1737
01:10:37,199 --> 01:10:39,568
-Put it on top like that.
-Like this?

1738
01:10:39,635 --> 01:10:42,004
-Then I eat it like this?
-Just like that.

1739
01:10:43,439 --> 01:10:45,741
HE CLOSES HIS EYES
AND TAKES A BITE

1740
01:10:45,808 --> 01:10:47,376
LAUGHING OUT LOUD

1741
01:10:47,443 --> 01:10:48,444
Come on.

1742
01:10:48,510 --> 01:10:51,547
He's such a born comedian.

1743
01:10:52,481 --> 01:10:54,817
-All right.
-What was that?

1744
01:10:54,883 --> 01:10:56,585
What's that facial expression?

1745
01:10:56,652 --> 01:10:58,787
-He gave him a glance.
-That face.

1746
01:10:58,854 --> 01:11:02,157
-He must be unsure.
-I don't think it goes with beer.

1747
01:11:02,224 --> 01:11:04,793
-He's not sure.
-He takes another bite.

1748
01:11:04,860 --> 01:11:06,195
He's checking once again.

1749
01:11:06,262 --> 01:11:07,896
I don't think he gets it.

1750
01:11:07,963 --> 01:11:10,099
Nam-no used

1751
01:11:10,165 --> 01:11:12,801
uncooked croissant dough to make that.

1752
01:11:13,502 --> 01:11:16,905
I love the texture of the croissant dough.
It's delicious.

1753
01:11:16,972 --> 01:11:19,275
-Well, it's delicious bread.
-It is.

1754
01:11:19,341 --> 01:11:21,477
And the meat.

1755
01:11:21,543 --> 01:11:22,645
The meat?

1756
01:11:22,711 --> 01:11:25,514
It feels like uncooked marinated bulgogi.

1757
01:11:25,581 --> 01:11:28,684
-Does it feel undercooked?
-Uncooked bulgogi?

1758
01:11:28,751 --> 01:11:31,487
Is this a way to eat beef?

1759
01:11:31,553 --> 01:11:33,656
-You said you liked beef tartare, so…
-Beef tartare?

1760
01:11:33,722 --> 01:11:36,158
<i>He just seared it lightly.</i>

1761
01:11:36,225 --> 01:11:38,460
<i>-He kept it undercooked.</i>
<i>-You should've said so.</i>

1762
01:11:38,527 --> 01:11:40,529
This feels like a premium dish.

1763
01:11:40,596 --> 01:11:42,231
-Wine.
-It'd go well with wine.

1764
01:11:42,298 --> 01:11:44,967
But he's trying to have beer at home.

1765
01:11:45,034 --> 01:11:46,935
-Try the salad.
-I will.

1766
01:11:47,002 --> 01:11:50,072
He made the salad in just 30 seconds.

1767
01:11:50,139 --> 01:11:52,308
He put it together in a hurry.

1768
01:11:52,374 --> 01:11:55,177
He wants a bar snack for himself
when he drinks beer alone.

1769
01:11:55,244 --> 01:11:57,579
HE EATS BOTH THE CHERRY TOMATO
AND ARUGULA IN ONE BITE

1770
01:11:58,147 --> 01:11:59,415
It must be citrusy.

1771
01:12:00,949 --> 01:12:03,886
-He's clapping.
-He's clapping.

1772
01:12:03,952 --> 01:12:05,821
-I'm glad.
-Do you like that?

1773
01:12:05,888 --> 01:12:08,557
It's really good.
What did you pour over it?

1774
01:12:08,624 --> 01:12:11,994
<i>It was just olive oil,</i>
<i>balsamic vinegar, and a bit of salt.</i>

1775
01:12:12,061 --> 01:12:14,029
This is just an ordinary salad, right?

1776
01:12:14,096 --> 01:12:15,230
-It's very good.
-Yes.

1777
01:12:16,598 --> 01:12:19,201
A HIGH PRAISE FOR HIS SIDE DISH

1778
01:12:19,268 --> 01:12:21,904
-I thought I'd easily win.
-I see.

1779
01:12:21,970 --> 01:12:24,440
-It doesn't have too many calories.
-It's a healthy choice.

1780
01:12:24,506 --> 01:12:26,275
-Yes.
-It's perfect with beer.

1781
01:12:26,342 --> 01:12:30,279
Let's try their dishes too.
This is Poong's Poong Goes On.

1782
01:12:30,346 --> 01:12:32,181
Please try the fried tofu.

1783
01:12:32,247 --> 01:12:36,118
-Sung-ju.
-I even like the one without sauce.

1784
01:12:36,685 --> 01:12:38,587
-This is good.
-It's sweet and spicy sauce.

1785
01:12:38,654 --> 01:12:40,222
-The sauce is spectacular.
-Yes.

1786
01:12:40,789 --> 01:12:42,291
I'm craving beer.

1787
01:12:42,358 --> 01:12:44,993
-Tofu is a healthy ingredient.
-Yes.

1788
01:12:45,060 --> 01:12:48,430
But it tastes unhealthy and delicious.

1789
01:12:49,565 --> 01:12:50,566
It does, right?

1790
01:12:50,632 --> 01:12:53,502
But it's really good.
I'm also craving beer.

1791
01:12:53,569 --> 01:12:58,574
That was excellent.
This time, Nam-no's No Beer Left Behind.

1792
01:12:59,141 --> 01:13:01,310
It's excellent.

1793
01:13:01,377 --> 01:13:03,812
It's good.

1794
01:13:03,879 --> 01:13:06,382
It does taste good. It feels premium.

1795
01:13:06,448 --> 01:13:08,016
-It's classy.
-It is.

1796
01:13:08,083 --> 01:13:10,753
-I'm craving soju.
-Yes, soju.

1797
01:13:10,819 --> 01:13:11,820
-Wine.
-He's Korean.

1798
01:13:11,887 --> 01:13:12,888
I'm craving wine.

1799
01:13:12,955 --> 01:13:15,190
-This isn't for beer.
-I want some soju.

1800
01:13:15,257 --> 01:13:17,659
I'll want to eat Chef Nam-no's dish
at a wine bar somewhere.

1801
01:13:17,726 --> 01:13:20,062
It would be really wonderful.

1802
01:13:20,129 --> 01:13:21,530
It's because he runs a wine bar.

1803
01:13:21,597 --> 01:13:24,800
-Yes, he runs a wine bar.
-It was just as he said.

1804
01:13:24,867 --> 01:13:28,871
Poong's dish was focused more on beer.

1805
01:13:28,937 --> 01:13:34,510
This would've been a good combination
with rosé sparkling wine.

1806
01:13:34,576 --> 01:13:35,611
Both were delicious.

1807
01:13:35,677 --> 01:13:38,847
Chef Nam-no's dish had

1808
01:13:38,914 --> 01:13:41,583
a great balance
for people who enjoy delicacies.

1809
01:13:41,650 --> 01:13:44,987
-He made it with ingredients like caviar.
-Yes.

1810
01:13:45,053 --> 01:13:46,889
-Yes.
-It'd go really well with wine.

1811
01:13:46,955 --> 01:13:50,025
-It's classy.
-But he wanted to eat it with beer.

1812
01:13:50,092 --> 01:13:53,796
This one is for regular beer,
and this one is for premium malt or ale.

1813
01:13:54,763 --> 01:13:59,034
-It'd go well with ale.
-Yes, either ale or premium malt.

1814
01:13:59,101 --> 01:14:00,969
-It's based on these.
-It's time to choose.

1815
01:14:01,036 --> 01:14:03,372
Press one for Yoon Nam-no.

1816
01:14:03,439 --> 01:14:05,674
Press two for Kim Poong.

1817
01:14:05,741 --> 01:14:07,376
-This is so hard.
-Please.

1818
01:14:07,443 --> 01:14:08,777
One for Nam-no, two for Poong.

1819
01:14:08,844 --> 01:14:10,379
Gosh, please!

1820
01:14:11,413 --> 01:14:13,782
Look how desperate he is.

1821
01:14:13,849 --> 01:14:17,686
-I'm desperate too! Come on, deities!
-Make your choice.

1822
01:14:17,753 --> 01:14:19,154
PLEASE, DEITY MYUNG-SOO

1823
01:14:19,221 --> 01:14:20,222
Make your choice

1824
01:14:21,190 --> 01:14:23,192
-and press the button.
-He must've pushed it.

1825
01:14:23,258 --> 01:14:24,827
Ugh!

1826
01:14:25,627 --> 01:14:26,628
He pressed it.

1827
01:14:26,695 --> 01:14:28,464
My staff are watching.

1828
01:14:28,530 --> 01:14:30,766
-My mom and dad are watching.
-I can't tell who'll win.

1829
01:14:31,433 --> 01:14:34,169
Let's find out which one
the cool-headed Myung-soo chose.

1830
01:14:34,236 --> 01:14:35,871
Show us the result.

1831
01:14:36,605 --> 01:14:39,141
Grandpa Myung-soo, alone with beer.

1832
01:14:39,208 --> 01:14:41,343
-Will Webtoon Artist Kim Poong…
-Darn it.

1833
01:14:41,410 --> 01:14:44,680
…win against Nam-no once again
and rise triumphantly?

1834
01:14:44,746 --> 01:14:48,717
Or will Nam-no win against Poong this time

1835
01:14:48,784 --> 01:14:51,186
and get his star?

1836
01:14:51,253 --> 01:14:53,455
-Oh, man.
-This was Nam-no's revenge.

1837
01:14:53,522 --> 01:14:56,458
Let's find out the result!

1838
01:14:56,959 --> 01:14:58,727
Who won this time?

1839
01:14:59,461 --> 01:15:02,331
Who did Myung-soo choose?

1840
01:15:02,397 --> 01:15:03,832
Who is it?

1841
01:15:03,899 --> 01:15:04,933
WHO DID MYUNG-SOO CHOOSE?

1842
01:15:06,802 --> 01:15:08,203
KIM POONG WINS

1843
01:15:08,270 --> 01:15:10,506
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
POONG GOES ON WINS

1844
01:15:10,572 --> 01:15:13,575
-My gosh.
-It's over.

1845
01:15:13,642 --> 01:15:17,045
-No!
-What will Nam-no do? He's done for.

1846
01:15:17,779 --> 01:15:20,582
-Stop lying. How can this happen?
-He lost twice in a row against Poong.

1847
01:15:20,649 --> 01:15:23,385
You should serve my dish at your bar.

1848
01:15:23,452 --> 01:15:25,220
I made myself clear.

1849
01:15:25,287 --> 01:15:28,323
-I said I drink alone.
-Exactly.

1850
01:15:28,390 --> 01:15:30,792
So when I eat the bar snack,
I need to crave more beer.

1851
01:15:30,859 --> 01:15:33,896
When I tried the sweet and spicy tofu,

1852
01:15:33,962 --> 01:15:36,899
the spiciness made me crave
the next sip of beer.

1853
01:15:36,965 --> 01:15:39,101
-He's right.
-It makes you crave beer.

1854
01:15:39,167 --> 01:15:42,204
But Chef Nam-no's dish was classy.

1855
01:15:42,271 --> 01:15:45,841
-It was.
-It'd go better with wine or champagne.

1856
01:15:45,908 --> 01:15:47,943
I think there was a misunderstanding.

1857
01:15:48,010 --> 01:15:52,147
-It's because…
-Chef Nam-no's name tag is coming off.

1858
01:15:52,214 --> 01:15:54,116
ABOUT TO DROP

1859
01:15:54,182 --> 01:15:55,717
I'm sorry.

1860
01:15:55,784 --> 01:15:57,419
I'm sorry, Chef Nam-no.

1861
01:15:57,486 --> 01:16:00,222
-He's in shock.
-It's about to fall off out of shock.

1862
01:16:00,289 --> 01:16:03,625
The maniac lost to Poong twice.

1863
01:16:03,692 --> 01:16:05,460
How do you feel, Poong?

1864
01:16:05,527 --> 01:16:09,898
I knew it. The maniac of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>

1865
01:16:09,965 --> 01:16:12,601
was me, Kim Poong!

1866
01:16:13,969 --> 01:16:17,205
He's happy to call himself a maniac.

1867
01:16:17,272 --> 01:16:20,976
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong
takes his third star!

1868
01:16:21,043 --> 01:16:22,578
Kim Poong wins!

1869
01:16:23,545 --> 01:16:27,783
-Please put a star on Poong, Myung-soo.
-It really was delicious.

1870
01:16:27,849 --> 01:16:30,886
Two of Poong's three stars are
from his matches against Nam-no.

1871
01:16:30,953 --> 01:16:31,954
It must be a lot of pressure.

1872
01:16:32,020 --> 01:16:35,657
-Poong takes his third win!
-Nam-no is crying.

1873
01:16:35,724 --> 01:16:38,460
-Congratulations!
-It was delicious.

1874
01:16:38,527 --> 01:16:41,997
Please welcome today's fridge owners,
Kim Nam-il and Lee Dong-gook!

1875
01:16:42,064 --> 01:16:44,466
The most popular guy
during the 2002 World Cup.

1876
01:16:44,533 --> 01:16:46,468
You were sensational,
and was on the news a lot.

1877
01:16:46,535 --> 01:16:47,736
Hey.

1878
01:16:47,803 --> 01:16:51,840
Hey, all of you. No, wait. I'm sorry.

1879
01:16:51,907 --> 01:16:54,009
You can just include me.

1880
01:16:54,076 --> 01:16:55,577
Don't hurt him like that.

1881
01:16:55,644 --> 01:16:57,813
We're here at <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Stadium.

1882
01:16:57,879 --> 01:16:59,414
Representing Korea, Kim Poong.

1883
01:16:59,481 --> 01:17:01,249
He's up against Fabri, an Italian.

1884
01:17:01,316 --> 01:17:02,718
-Go, Korea!
-Go, Korea!

1885
01:17:04,386 --> 01:17:05,621
The skin got inside.

1886
01:17:05,687 --> 01:17:06,888
Nam-il's warning.

1887
01:17:06,955 --> 01:17:08,056
Can I use the sifter?

1888
01:17:08,123 --> 01:17:09,391
You're cheating!

1889
01:17:09,458 --> 01:17:11,927
Referee Kim Nam-il cards him right away.

1890
01:17:11,994 --> 01:17:13,996
We need to flush this one too.

1891
01:17:14,062 --> 01:17:15,330
It's so shocking.

1892
01:17:15,397 --> 01:17:17,866
<i>I looked up to Chef Hyun-suk</i>
<i>as I aspired to be a chef.</i>

1893
01:17:17,933 --> 01:17:20,802
I want to win against the final boss
as the <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> kid.

1894
01:17:20,869 --> 01:17:22,037
Why is she going that far?

1895
01:17:22,104 --> 01:17:23,338
My lid is gone.

1896
01:17:23,405 --> 01:17:25,474
Chef Hyun-suk,
you aren't using this, right?

1897
01:17:25,540 --> 01:17:26,875
-Can you take this off?
-Okay.

1898
01:17:26,942 --> 01:17:29,411
-The industry lacks discipline now.
-He's shaken up.

1899
01:17:29,478 --> 01:17:33,115
The vacuum cleaner sucks in everything!

1900
01:17:33,181 --> 01:17:37,319
-Kim Nam-il!
-The vacuum cleaner finished it!

1901
01:17:38,587 --> 01:17:39,888
KIM POONG MAGIC, COMING SOON

1902
01:17:50,966 --> 01:17:55,971
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
